; Dungeon — level 1, static layer (structure and fixtures).
; One character per cell; every row must be the same width.
; Lines starting with ';' and blank lines are ignored.
;
;   #  solid rock          .  floor
;   P  party start         D  dusty floor (air turbidity 1)
;   T  wall torch sconce   F  fire brazier (blocks movement)
;
; Grid glyphs are never lowercase: lines starting with a lowercase letter
; are records. "textures" records declare the level's surface texture
; palette — the game loads only the sets named here (each needs its worn
; block meshes baked, see ModelBaker.cpp); "decoration" records are static
; entities (see Entity.h for the format), e.g.
;   decoration banner 4 2 north
; Dynamic content — monsters, items, buttons — lives in level1.ent.

textures wall wall_brick wall_stone wall_moss
textures floor floor_slabs floor_cobble
textures ceiling ceiling_rough ceiling_cracked
;
; Fires raise the air turbidity of their own and nearby squares.
; The lower-left block (rows 12-14) is the dust-shaft showcase: a dusty
; chamber with two freestanding columns, a wall torch behind them, and
; the mummy backlit beside it.
################
#P.....T#......#
#.#####..#.###.#
#.#....#.#.#T#.#
#.#.##.#.#.#.#.#
#.#.#TF#.#.#.#.#
#.#.####.#.#.#.#
#........#...#.#
#.########.###.#
#DDD.....#.#..F#
########D#.#.###
#TDDD.DDD#.#..T#
#DDDDD.D#..##..#
#DD#D#DT#.#..#.#
#DD.DDD#..F#...#
################
;
; Static decorations (see ModelBaker.cpp for the prop set; <type>.gltf).
; Format: decoration <type> <x> <z> [facing] [key=value]. All props block the
; party except open passages (the archway); add solid=0 to make any prop walk-
; through. The lower-left dusty chamber is furnished as a showcase.
decoration archway 4 1 east solid=0
decoration fountain 3 12 south
decoration column 1 12 south
decoration column 5 11 south
decoration statue 6 12 west
decoration chest 1 13 south
decoration barrel 1 14 south
decoration crate 2 14 south
decoration door 8 4 south
; imported authored model (AssetBaker import-model) — textured + back-culled
decoration ancient_pot 6 1 south
